# Regression: pytest.run RECOGNIZES a requirements.txt-only project as a
# valid Python project (matches pyright's LSP root_markers).
#
# History: 2026-06-28 3rd multilang-dev-user pass found that pytest.run
# was toasting "no pyproject.toml / setup.py / test files" on a project
# with requirements.txt (and pyright happily attaching) — contradictory
# signals to the user. Fixed by adding requirements.txt to the detect
# set in src/app/playwright.rs::run_pytest.
#
# This fixture locks the fix: with only requirements.txt + a test file,
# pytest.run should NOT emit the "no manifest" toast.

shell echo 'flask==3.0.0\npytest==8.0.0' > requirements.txt
shell mkdir -p src
shell echo 'def main(): pass' > src/app.py
shell mkdir -p tests
shell echo 'def test_it(): assert True' > tests/test_app.py

command pytest.run
wait 50
# The "no pyproject / setup.py / requirements.txt / test files" toast
# must NOT appear — requirements.txt + tests/test_*.py is enough.
expect screen lacks "no pyproject.toml"
